snippet.textDisplay:
I've been listening to 'Tajdar-e-Haram' for the past one hour. First, the original by Sabri Brothers, then the cover by Amjad Sabri, and, finally, this amazing rendition by Atif Aslam. I highly recommend folks to take a journey through time like this. If you don't end up crying along the way, then just know there's something wrong with you.

For Muslims, well, the yearning to go see the beautiful Prophet's Mosque and pay your respects to the Greatest Human Being that ever lived will only get stronger.

May the Almighty forgive Amjad Sabri and his legendary father and uncle, and grant them the highest place in heaven.

And, lastly, may the killer of Amjad Sabri rot in the lowest depths of hell for extinguishing such a beautiful life.
